From 5d85972e56115b50f27dd5be361efc9ba4e8ecca Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harsh Kumar Bijlani <hbijlani@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Sep 2025 18:15:05 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k: Avoid setting ath12k_dp_peer to NULL
 within ath12k_dp_link_peer

struct ath12k_dp_link_peer has a backpointer "dp_peer" which points to
the parent object ath12k_dp_peer. This backpointer to set to NULL in
the API ath12k_dp_link_peer_unassign during the delete of link_peer.

There can be cases wherein ath12k_dp_link_peer is found in the linked
list after unassignment and dp_peer is accessed which results in NULL
pointer access and device goes for a crash.

In order to handle this, avoid resetting of dp_peer within
ath12k_dp_link_peer in the unassignment path as ath12k_dp_peer is the
last object to be deleted in the peer delete flow.

Patch-dependency: 0116-0002-wifi-ath12k-Attach-and-detach-ath12k_dp_link_peer-to.patch

Signed-off-by: Harsh Kumar Bijlani <hbijlani@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c
index e9d30d2..f2ed6ae 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_peer.c
@@ -763,8 +763,6 @@ void ath12k_dp_link_peer_unassign(struct ath12k *ar, u8 vdev_id, u8 *addr)
 	if (temp_peer && temp_peer->hw_link_id == ar->hw_link_id)
 		ath12k_dp_link_peer_rhash_delete(dp, peer);
 
-	peer->dp_peer = NULL;
-
 	spin_unlock_bh(&dp->dp_lock);
 
 	synchronize_rcu();
-- 
